race.comment: ROLLING MAGIC (7) consistent gelding who was just under three weeks between runs when nailed late with the 57.5kg to finish second to Alabama Fox over 1500m at this track. Gets map favours and the booking of Josh Parr can see him go one better. JAMBEROO (8) covered plenty of ground in the run and never shirked his task when second over the mile in the Nowra Cup. Has the gate speed to negate a tricky draw. Drops in weight and shapes as the main danger. WELCOMETOTHESHOW (6) comes up from Victoria in sparkling form, winning his last three starts in good fashion. Rounded them up effortlessly from back in the field with plenty up the sleeve over 1600m at Flemington. Impossible to knock the form and will go well again. DANCES WITH HOOVES (11) impressive winner of the Mudgee Cup two-back, then failed to get into the contest when a plugging seventh over 1600m at this track. Down sharply in weight and anywhere near her best can win this. SUN GOD (3) hard fit and keep safe from the wide gate.
